Picturing Jayproto, Ceto, and Biskett in a somewhat ethereal place :3

Jayproto's alternative fursona: Jaykitty!

Comfy cozy.. ideal living room...
Misty Palisades, as my sister created the name for many many years ago, not knowing what "palisades" were. I rendered this joke image as a parody.
Was feeling very exhausted one night, but still creative, so I depicted Lecks in a soft location...
Lecks refsheet :33
Low-poly render of a slightly more outdoors scene

Very dark cross-section of a pool... used as a channel banner for my alternative YouTube account
A re-render of my first ever poolrooms chamber with the materials I was using at the time
My first ever poolrooms render, redone with modern materials and composition
Other side of the close-ceilinged tunnel of the October 29th render
Pointed entrances are a motif that I often see in backrooms "exploration" found-footage style videos
Enter the dangerous waters through the back way of the facility...
Verticality is often not played with enough in these renders...
Original version of this... was obsessed with simple bar lighting (opposed to magicl floating point lights)
As long as you're in the warm lighting, you're safe...
-This was the render where I realized my tile normals were backwards for the past thirty renders...
Maybe a ten-minute project of benchmarking how fast I could make a render
The classic spiral staircase... don't slip!
And you better hope those steps are reinforced! Could just happen to be that nobody's used them yet...
I could not get the Danger Zone to look right; the tiles had to be light blue otherwise the scene would be too dark
Red accent walls.. pops a little when you look at it
The fog in this render reminds me of Silent Hill
Finally got the look of the danger zone...
-Just needed white grout in the tiles
The danger zone tunnel gradually sinks below the surface
-Who knows how far it continues down? It could go ten feet or a mile... What could live down there?
Inspired by the storm drains in Tokyo... except with pool tiles instead, making it swimmable!
My attempt at recreating one of the classic Jared Pike dreampools renders
This was originally meant to be a pillar of water falling, but it looks better as a glass tube
-The light in the room is carried by the water from the sky above...
Large, shallow, wavy pool... lit by circular lights for pi day!
Something could just reach out from the darkness...
Don't look too long...
Vast geometric poolroom chamber
Not-so-grand arches...
Always had a strange obsession with including wavy tile walls like this in my renders

Started experimentation with different materials and object to spice things up...

Lotta pool floaties... and interesting yellow walls...
